reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 3, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Review of All Ahead Full: Jesse McDermitt series Book 22
reviews.reviewText: An excellent story with plenty of suspense and lots of villains. The setting is Honduras in the jungles. What is threatened is the indigenous tribes in the jungle, the jungle itself, and the wildlife that live there. The drug cartels are capturing and selling wildlife, clearing the jungle and selling off trees that are in demand for their hardwood, and planting cocoa to produce huge quantities of cocaine. Environmentalists become targets to eliminate and anyone who stands in their way. Jesse McDermitt decides to get involved to stop it and gets the green light from Jack Armstrong. Quite the story, one wishes all drug cartels were dealt with this way!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 19, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Hatch or a door?
reviews.reviewText: I've read many of the Jesse McDermitt novels and have enjoyed them immensely. The only thing that bothers me is his misuse of the term"hatch" when referring to a door. As a maritime professional we use the term hatch when referring to an opening in the deck,where personnel or other items pass thru vertically. Even a watertight door is still referred to as a door on a yacht or ship.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A new direction
reviews.reviewText: When I first encountered Stinnett's Jesse McDermott in the first book, he was newly retired from active duty as a Marine. He made his way to the Florida Keys and began living as a civilian. Over the course of twenty plus books, he married, lost his wife, gained friends, reunited with his daughters, worked for Homeland Security, killed a few bad guys, saved a bunch of people, married again and, most recently , moved.out of his island life and into a 199 foot yacht cum research vessel.There's an ongoing cast of characters - the result of Stinnett's skill at world building. I don't think you need to know all the backstory from all the previous books, but I am happy to say I've followed all of them and this one is whole and complete and also sets the stage for the next book to.come. I look forward to it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Just picked this one up after taking a break from the series. It's easy to get into the characters and flow of the story. Fast paced and focusing on some important topics Jesse and his crew take matters in their own hands and we all know how this ends.If you have not started this series pick up book 1 and get started if you like sailing, Florida Keys, tropical islands and lots of action with detailed military knowledge.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2021
reviews.reviewText: Jesse's new life is a world away from his home in the Content Keys. I enjoy his evolving inclusion in making the world a better place, along with his family. Learning about new places and cultures is an absolute benefit of reading about Jesse's adventures. I am excited to learn that Deuce and company will be returning when Phoenix is christened. Another great book by a wonderful author! I, for one, am glad Wayne Stinnett decided to take a chance on an old dream of becoming an author!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Another Great Story!
reviews.reviewText: All Ahead Full is another great story about Jesse and friends coming to help out in a big way where people are being exploited. He and his crew and friends are highly skilled, intelligent and caring people. This world needs more people like that. Can't wait for #23! Thank you Mr. Stinnett. I truly have enjoyed each and every one of your books.

Amazing read from start to finish. Couldn’t put it down as always!! These characters are just like family and you can’t wait for the next book!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on December 9, 2021
reviews.reviewText: Another fantastic book from Wayne as he brought back some of the old squad from earlier book's it was nice to read about what they are now doing and what they still do.
I especially love the surprise at the end with the power plants!The more people that know about them the better!(Yes I fully understand and support that technology! Thank you!)
Wayne, these just keep getting better. Be careful readers, once you pick it up you just can't put it down.
